  -- In particular, set v₀ := p w - x (but note p 0 = x, so this is like the derivative direction).
  -- However, a cleaner approach: because the diffeology is fine, the plot p is smooth, so its derivative
  -- at 0 exists. Let v₀ := fderiv ℝ p 0 w. Then by the fundamental relation in the tangent space,
  -- lof p w = lof (λ t, x + t • v₀) 1.
